{"url": "http://computableplant.ics.uci.edu/BGRS-2002-KAP-abstract.html", "content": "<html version=\"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN\">\n<head>\n\n<link REL=\"SHORTCUT ICON\" href=\"favicon.ico\"> \n<title>The Computable Plant</title>\n\n\n<style type=\"text/css\">\n  <!--\n    a:link {text-decoration:none; color:blue;}\n    a:visited {text-decoration:none; color:blue;}\n    a:active {text-decoration:none; background-color:yellow; color:black; }\n    a:hover {text-decoration:none; background-color:yellow; color:black; }\n    a.nav:link {text-decoration:none; background-color:purple;color:white;}\n    a.nav:visited {text-decoration:none; background-color:purple;color:yellow;}\n    a.nav:active {text-decoration:none; background-color:blue; color:white; }\n    a.nav:hover {text-decoration:none; background-color:blue; color:white; }\n    .title {font-style:italic; color:purple;}\n    ul.nsf li {list-style-image: url(\"img/nsfbullet.gif\")}\n    .button { \n  border-top: 1px dotted #888888;\n  border-bottom: 1px dotted #888888;\n  border-right: 1px dotted #888888;\n  border-left: 1px dotted #888888;\n  padding-top: 1pt; \n  padding-bottom: 1pt; \n  text-align: center;background:#C0C0C0;\n}\n -->\n</style>\n\n\n\n</HEAD>\n<BODY>\n\n<a name=\"top\">\n\n<!-- Navigation Bar -->\n<center>\n\t<table width=\"640\" border=0 style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold; font-family:arial;font-size:36pt;color:white;background:purple;\">\n\t\t<tr><td style=\"font-size:large;text-align:center;\">Scientific Inference Systems Laboratory</td></tr>\n\t\t<tr><td style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"text-align:center;\">The Computable Plant</span></td></tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t<td align=center style=\"font-family:verdana,arial,helvetica; font-size:small; color:white; \">\n\t\t\t<a class=\"nav\" href=\"index.html\">Home</a> |  \n\t\t\t<a class=\"nav\" href=\"publications.html\">Publications</a> | \n\t\t\t<a class=\"nav\" href=\"research.html\">Research</a> | \n\t\t\t<a class=\"nav\" href=\"gallery.html\">Gallery</a> | \n\t\t\t<a class=\"nav\" href=\"people.html\">People</a> | \n\t\t\t<a class=\"nav\" href=\"outreach.html\">Outreach</a> |\n\t\t\t<a class=\"nav\" href=\"sw.html\">Software</a> |\n\t\t\t<a class=\"nav\" href=\"links.html\">Links</a> |\n\t\t\t<a class=\"nav\" href=\"tut.html\">Tutorials</a> \n\t\t</td>\n\n\t\t</tr>\n\n\t</table>\n</center>\n<!-- End of Navigation Bar -->\n<!-- Page Content Starts Here -->\n\n\n<div style=\"font-family:verdana,arial,helvetica; font-size:small; color:black; \">\n\n<center>\n\t<table border=\"0\" width=\"640\">\n\t\t<tr>\n\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" >\n\n\t\t\t\t<div style=\"text-align:left;font-family:arial;font-size:x-large;color:purple;background:#C0C0C0;\"><p>\n\t\t\tModeling Plant Development with Gene Regulation Networks Including Signaling and Cell Division\n\t\t\t\t</p></div>\n\n\n\t\t\t\t<div style=\"text-align:left;font-family:arial;font-size:large;color:purple;\"><p>\n\t\t\t\tHenrik J&ouml;nsson, Bruce E. Shapiro, Elliot M. Meyerowitz, Eric Mjolsness\n\t\t\t\t</p></div>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div style=\"text-align:left;font-family:arial;font-size:medium;color:purple;\"><p>\n\t\t\t\tIn: <i>Bioinformatics of Genome Regulation and Structure</i>, ed. N. A. Kolchanov, Kluwer Publications, pp. 311-318 (2004).\u0000\n\t\t\t\t</p></div>\n\t\n\t\t\t\t<div style=\"text-align:left;font-family:arial;font-size:large;color:purple;\">\n\t\t\t\t<p>Abstract</p>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\n\n\t\t\t\t<div style=\"text-align:justify;font-family:arial;font-size:small;color:purple;\">\n\n<p>The shoot apical meristem of Arabidopsis thaliana is an example of a developmental system which can be modeled at genetic and mechanical levels provided that suitable mathematical and computational tools are available to represent intercellular signaling, cell cycling, mechanical stresses, and a changing topology of neighborhood relationships between compartments.\n  </p><p>    In this paper we present a simplified dynamical 2-dimensional model of a growing plant. Cells in the shoot grow and proliferate, while the number of stem cells at the apex stays constant due to differentiation into tissue cells. Cell types are defined by protein concentrations within the cells, and the dynamics of the differentiation follows from a gene regulation network which includes intercellular signals.\n\n</p>\n\n</div>\n\n\n</td></tr>\n\t</table>\n</center>\n\n\n\n\n\n</HTML>", "encoding": "ascii"}